20049003@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The IRS warnings stem from a 1984 law that requires anyone who receives more than $10,000 in cash from a client or customer in one or more related transactions "in the course of trade or business" to report the payment on a document known as Form 8300.@@@@1@47@@oe@2-2-2013
